            {
              "text": "{\"confidence\": 0.82, \"suggestions\": [\"Implement a 3-day attribution window in your analytics to capture the full conversion cycle\", \"Prioritize session-driving campaigns (organic, paid search, social) since sessions are a strong revenue predictor\", \"Monitor session quality metrics (bounce rate, session duration) to ensure volume gains translate to revenue\", \"Test increasing marketing spend in top-performing traffic sources to validate the 0.85 coefficient at higher volumes\", \"Create cohort analysis comparing Day 1 sessions to Day 3-4 conversions to understand the buying journey\", \"Set up automated alerts for session drops, given the strong correlation to revenue outcomes\"], \"summary\": \"Strong positive correlation (0.85) between sessions and revenue with a 3-day lag indicates customers typically convert 3 days after initial session. This suggests a deliberate consideration phase in your buying cycle. Focus on session acquisition quality and volume, and attribute revenue to marketing efforts with a 3-day lookback window for accurate ROI measurement.\"}",
